description: a(n)^3 is smallest cube containing exactly n 8's.
links: Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Cubic Number
mathematica: a[n_] := Module[{i = 0}, While[DigitCount[i^3][[8]] != n, i++ ]; i] - Sam Handler (sam_5_5_5_0(AT)yahoo.com), Aug 29 2006
